02:01:37.280 --> 02:01:38.900
Definition of accounting costs.

02:01:38.980 --> 02:01:40.560
Please look at the slide.

02:01:42.060 --> 02:01:45.060
Accounting costs of a company are

02:01:45.060 --> 02:01:50.650
the amount of actual payments purchased

02:01:50.790 --> 02:01:52.730
by resources.

02:01:52.830 --> 02:01:54.010
Well, that is very easy.

02:01:54.930 --> 02:01:59.460
To produce something, a company

02:01:59.460 --> 02:02:03.260
needs a variety of resources.

02:02:03.880 --> 02:02:06.880
This company purchases.

02:02:06.980 --> 02:02:10.360
A accountant then summarizes all these

02:02:10.360 --> 02:02:11.560
payments purchased by resources

02:02:11.560 --> 02:02:15.660
and enters them into its accounting

02:02:15.660 --> 02:02:18.020
report.

02:02:19.480 --> 02:02:24.600
Let us look at the simplest

02:02:24.600 --> 02:02:26.320
example.

02:02:26.420 --> 02:02:28.820
Let us look at the simplest

02:02:28.820 --> 02:02:32.420
example of accounting costs.

