02:02:45.840 --> 02:02:47.980
The entire cost of the equipment

02:02:47.980 --> 02:02:50.040
cannot be attributed to the

02:02:50.040 --> 02:02:51.140
cost of one year.

02:02:52.000 --> 02:02:54.320
We need to use amortization.

02:02:54.880 --> 02:02:57.120
When using the simplest linear

02:02:57.120 --> 02:02:59.980
depreciation, the cost of one

02:02:59.980 --> 02:03:02.360
year will be attributed, respectively,

02:03:02.360 --> 02:03:04.840
200, divided by 5, 40

02:03:04.840 --> 02:03:06.640
rubles.

02:03:07.320 --> 02:03:17.140
The accountant makes its report.

02:03:17.460 --> 02:03:21.040
The amortisation is 40 rubles.

02:03:21.140 --> 02:03:25.620
Further, let's say, a firm uses an

02:03:25.720 --> 02:03:31.160
annual accountant writing 80 raw materials

02:03:31.160 --> 02:03:36.220
and paying a firm, let's say, 60

02:03:36.220 --> 02:03:50.420
rubles of salary per year.

02:03:50.420 --> 02:03:56.640
The accountant says, salary 60.

02:03:56.740 --> 02:03:58.460
Now let's say that

02:03:58.560 --> 02:04:02.040
the equipment is 20 rubles.

02:04:03.520 --> 02:04:05.700
The annual loan

02:04:05.700 --> 02:04:08.480
rate is 20 rubles.

02:04:09.960 --> 02:04:12.640
The loan fee is 20 rubles.

02:04:13.720 --> 02:04:16.880
Suppose that no more payments are

02:04:16.880 --> 02:04:19.580
made by the company.

02:04:20.340 --> 02:04:22.680
Well, it does not incur administrative,

02:04:22.940 --> 02:04:24.820
transportation, advertising, research,

02:04:25.120 --> 02:04:27.200
does not pay taxes and is not

02:04:27.200 --> 02:04:28.580
attributable to cost.

02:04:29.060 --> 02:04:31.180
Nothing of that.

02:04:32.560 --> 02:04:34.660
The accountant summarizes all these

02:04:34.660 --> 02:04:36.320
payments and writes.

02:04:40.600 --> 02:04:42.680
The accounting costs amounted

02:04:42.680 --> 02:04:45.640
