02:24:00.920 --> 02:24:05.060
We start with the third question, the types of costs.

02:24:07.380 --> 02:24:10.180
All costs, both accounting and

02:24:10.720 --> 02:24:13.520
complete economic, can be divided

02:24:13.520 --> 02:24:17.880
into constant and variable.

02:24:19.940 --> 02:24:22.100
What is at the basis of this division?

02:24:22.420 --> 02:24:24.140
See here.

02:24:24.820 --> 02:24:28.100
The company is increasing the production.

02:24:31.070 --> 02:24:34.950
And it is evident that with the increase of

02:24:34.950 --> 02:24:39.690
output, some costs change, while

02:24:39.690 --> 02:24:41.010
others remain unchanged.

02:24:41.430 --> 02:24:45.350
The costs that do not change with

02:24:45.350 --> 02:24:48.970
the increase in output are

02:24:48.970 --> 02:24:51.110
called fixed costs.

02:24:51.110 --> 02:24:54.650
The costs that change with the

02:24:54.650 --> 02:24:57.950
increase in output are called

02:24:57.950 --> 02:25:00.110
variable costs.

02:25:00.210 --> 02:25:03.110
Why are costs divided into constant

02:25:03.110 --> 02:25:04.810
and variable?

02:25:06.330 --> 02:25:09.630
Because we also divide the factors of

02:25:09.630 --> 02:25:13.170
production into constant and variable.

02:25:13.530 --> 02:25:16.710
The fact is that some factors

02:25:16.710 --> 02:25:20.150
of production can be changed easily

02:25:20.150 --> 02:25:22.590
and quickly with an increase

02:25:22.590 --> 02:25:23.630
in output.

02:25:23.810 --> 02:25:24.950
To increase the issue.

02:25:26.310 --> 02:25:28.590
Well, let's say, it's quite easy to hire

02:25:28.590 --> 02:25:31.110
new employees in the company.

02:25:32.490 --> 02:25:34.450
Workers are a variable factor

02:25:34.450 --> 02:25:35.570
of production.

02:25:35.570 --> 02:25:38.550
But the company takes a certain

02:25:38.550 --> 02:25:41.430
amount of time to purchase

02:25:41.430 --> 02:25:43.650
new equipment, that is, to use

02:25:43.650 --> 02:25:45.930
additional capital.

02:25:46.410 --> 02:25:48.290
Therefore, we usually refer equipment

02:25:48.290 --> 02:25:51.350
to a constant factor of production

02:25:51.350 --> 02:25:54.290
in a short period of time.

02:25:55.750 --> 02:25:58.550
Look at the definition again on the

02:25:58.550 --> 02:25:59.730
slide.

02:26:00.550 --> 02:26:03.430
Fixed costs are costs that

02:26:03.490 --> 02:26:06.270
do not change with the

02:26:06.270 --> 02:26:08.350
change in output.

02:26:09.090 --> 02:26:11.910
This is the cost of constant factors

02:26:11.910 --> 02:26:13.290
of production.

02:26:14.450 --> 02:26:16.490
Usually, the fixed costs

02:26:16.490 --> 02:26:19.130
include depreciation, rent,

02:26:19.130 --> 02:26:21.170
interest on the loan,

02:26:21.970 --> 02:26:23.610
and management salary.

02:26:24.130 --> 02:26:25.710
Unclear costs are also

02:26:25.710 --> 02:26:27.390
usually fixed.

02:26:28.610 --> 02:26:31.290
Now the variable costs again.

02:26:31.550 --> 02:26:33.690
Variable costs are costs whose

02:26:33.750 --> 02:26:36.410
value changes with the change

02:26:36.410 --> 02:26:37.410
in output.

02:26:38.050 --> 02:26:40.530
This is the cost of variable factors

02:26:40.530 --> 02:26:41.730
of production.

02:26:42.790 --> 02:26:44.890
These usually include wages in workers'

02:26:44.890 --> 02:26:46.810
production, raw materials and

02:26:47.370 --> 02:26:49.270
materials costs, electricity

02:26:49.690 --> 02:26:51.370
for technological purposes

02:26:51.370 --> 02:26:53.150
and others.

02:26:56.900 --> 02:27:00.580
Fixed costs and variable

02:27:00.580 --> 02:27:02.840
costs.

02:27:06.240 --> 02:27:08.540
If we summarize them, we

02:27:08.540 --> 02:27:11.620
get the total cost.

