02:51:44.200 --> 02:51:46.500
The average and fixed costs are always

02:51:46.510 --> 02:51:47.500
decreasing.

02:51:47.960 --> 02:51:49.300
There is nothing new here.

02:51:50.960 --> 02:51:54.040
The functions of the average variable

02:51:54.050 --> 02:51:57.280
and average total costs change

02:51:57.290 --> 02:51:58.300
immediately.

02:52:00.260 --> 02:52:02.880
Look what they will be now.

02:52:07.930 --> 02:52:09.630
Here is the slide.

02:52:11.050 --> 02:52:15.950
Limit and average costs.

02:52:15.960 --> 02:52:18.910
Look at what happens with

02:52:18.920 --> 02:52:20.650
the limit costs.

02:52:22.180 --> 02:52:23.760
As I said, first they decrease,

02:52:23.770 --> 02:52:26.900
then they reach the minimum, then

02:52:26.910 --> 02:52:29.860
they begin to strive, then they increase.

02:52:30.820 --> 02:52:33.200
What happens to the average

02:52:33.210 --> 02:52:35.020
variable cost?

02:52:36.000 --> 02:52:37.600
They first fall.

02:52:38.860 --> 02:52:40.700
But they are declining, as you

02:52:40.980 --> 02:52:44.400
can see, slower than the limit costs.

02:52:44.580 --> 02:52:45.420
Then look at.

02:52:45.680 --> 02:52:49.700
Within a certain period of time, the

02:52:49.710 --> 02:52:52.680
limit costs are already increasing.

02:52:54.080 --> 02:52:57.260
And the average variable costs,

02:53:00.130 --> 02:53:02.360
look carefully, they are still decreasing.

02:53:04.740 --> 02:53:08.000
And note that the average variable

02:53:08.010 --> 02:53:11.760
costs decrease until they

02:53:11.770 --> 02:53:15.220
are even above the limit costs.

02:53:16.920 --> 02:53:18.200
Hence the most important conclusion.

02:53:19.680 --> 02:53:23.280
The average variable cost

02:53:23.290 --> 02:53:26.180
reaches its minimum at

02:53:26.190 --> 02:53:31.040
the point where it is equal to

02:53:31.050 --> 02:53:32.720
the limit cost.

02:53:36.620 --> 02:53:40.460
Finally, let's look at the average

02:53:40.470 --> 02:53:42.260
total cost function.

02:53:46.340 --> 02:53:48.640
This function comes out of infinity.

02:53:49.160 --> 02:53:51.500
For an infinite small quantity,

02:53:51.510 --> 02:53:53.880
the average total cost is very large

02:53:53.890 --> 02:53:56.140
because the output is very small.

02:53:57.800 --> 02:53:58.480
Next What?

02:53:59.420 --> 02:54:03.440
They decline and also necessarily

02:54:03.450 --> 02:54:07.160
reach their minimum at the point where

02:54:07.220 --> 02:54:11.240
they are equal to the limit costs.

02:54:11.640 --> 02:54:14.820
The function of the limit costs necessarily

02:54:14.830 --> 02:54:18.640
crosses the functions of the average

02:54:18.650 --> 02:54:21.060
variable and the average total

02:54:21.070 --> 02:54:25.380
cost at the points of their minimum.

02:54:28.680 --> 02:54:30.360
Once the minimum point is

02:54:30.370 --> 02:54:33.040
passed, the average total

02:54:33.050 --> 02:54:36.840
cost begins to rise.

02:54:37.040 --> 02:54:41.920
As they increase, they are constantly

02:54:41.930 --> 02:54:45.940
approaching the function of

02:54:45.950 --> 02:54:47.440
average variable costs.

02:54:49.280 --> 02:54:50.660
Think, why is it so?

02:54:53.500 --> 02:54:55.980
The average total cost is equal

02:54:55.990 --> 02:54:58.340
to what we have already mentioned,

02:55:05.080 --> 02:55:08.360
the average constant cost, plus

02:55:08.370 --> 02:55:12.060
the average variable cost.

02:55:12.300 --> 02:55:15.440
What are the average constant

02:55:15.450 --> 02:55:16.220
costs?

02:55:18.630 --> 02:55:19.230
to zero.

02:55:19.590 --> 02:55:20.770
I have said this many times.

02:55:21.670 --> 02:55:25.470
The average variable cost

02:55:25.480 --> 02:55:30.330
is the average total cost.

02:55:31.110 --> 02:55:34.030
Well, this is actually all about

02:55:34.040 --> 02:55:36.530
the fourth issue of this topic –

02:55:36.540 --> 02:55:38.190
the cost in the short term.

02:55:40.140 --> 02:55:42.560
There is another fifth issue on the subject

02:55:42.570 --> 02:55:44.580
– the costs in the long term.

02:55:45.280 --> 02:55:47.240
There will be nothing new there,

02:55:47.250 --> 02:55:50.360
except that I just want

02:55:50.370 --> 02:55:53.760
to emphasize that there

02:55:53.770 --> 02:55:58.020
are no constant costs in

02:55:58.030 --> 02:55:59.200
the long run.

02:56:00.480 --> 02:56:03.280
All costs are variable.

02:56:03.300 --> 02:56:03.800
Why is?

02:56:05.860 --> 02:56:10.340
Because in the long run, the company

02:56:10.350 --> 02:56:13.640
can change all the factors of production.

02:56:14.080 --> 02:56:15.260
She can find additional

02:56:15.270 --> 02:56:17.460
workers, she can install additional

02:56:17.470 --> 02:56:19.420
equipment, she can rent

02:56:19.430 --> 02:56:22.840
a more spacious

02:56:22.850 --> 02:56:24.180
building.

02:56:25.220 --> 02:56:26.880
All factors of production

02:56:26.890 --> 02:56:29.040
become variable, so all

02:56:29.050 --> 02:56:32.600
costs also become variable.

02:56:33.080 --> 02:56:36.920
There is no function of average

02:56:36.930 --> 02:56:37.960
constant cost.

02:56:38.520 --> 02:56:40.180
Is there only a function?

02:56:41.020 --> 02:56:43.860
The function of the limit costs is the function

02:56:43.870 --> 02:56:45.820
of the average cost.

02:56:46.660 --> 02:56:47.860
And it will be the same.

02:56:48.560 --> 02:56:50.500
The function of the limit costs first

02:56:50.510 --> 02:56:53.740
decreases, then reaches a minimum,

02:56:53.750 --> 02:56:56.460
then begins to increase.

02:56:56.720 --> 02:56:59.560
The average total cost function first

02:56:59.570 --> 02:57:02.560
decreases, then reaches the minimum

02:57:02.570 --> 02:57:04.680
at the point of intersection

02:57:04.690 --> 02:57:07.860
with the limit cost function.

02:57:08.520 --> 02:57:10.200
After that, the average total

02:57:10.210 --> 02:57:13.860
cost function begins to increase.

02:57:21.150 --> 02:57:24.050
Let us start with the fourth topic

02:57:24.060 --> 02:57:25.570
of our course.

02:57:26.490 --> 02:57:29.790
Market Structures and Company Behavior.

02:57:30.210 --> 02:57:33.370
Here we will talk about how the company

02:57:33.380 --> 02:57:35.470
operates in certain market

02:57:35.480 --> 02:57:37.070
conditions.

02:57:38.430 --> 02:57:40.330
And it is probably obvious

02:57:40.340 --> 02:57:43.470
that the behavior of a company depends

02:57:43.480 --> 02:57:45.390
not only on the amount of

02:57:45.400 --> 02:57:48.290
resources it has, but also on the

02:57:48.300 --> 02:57:51.130
market environment in which it operates.

02:57:51.810 --> 02:57:54.410
In other words, the behavior of the company

02:57:54.420 --> 02:57:56.190
depends on the type of market.

02:57:56.910 --> 02:57:59.090
Please look at the slide.

02:57:59.100 --> 02:58:01.270
The first question we will discuss

02:58:01.280 --> 02:58:03.310
with you is called “types of

02:58:03.320 --> 02:58:05.650
market structures”.

02:58:05.660 --> 02:58:09.070
Or it will be about types of markets.

02:58:10.940 --> 02:58:13.940
Please see, there is...

02:58:13.950 --> 02:58:16.400
Microeconomics distinguishes four types

02:58:16.410 --> 02:58:19.020
of market structures or forms of market

02:58:19.030 --> 02:58:20.700
organization.

02:58:21.120 --> 02:58:24.700
This is perfect competition,

02:58:25.280 --> 02:58:28.380
monopoly, oligopoly,

02:58:28.680 --> 02:58:30.700
monopolistic competition.

02:58:35.550 --> 02:58:38.110
Let's start with perfect competition.

02:58:39.470 --> 02:58:41.730
Well, very often perfect

02:58:41.740 --> 02:58:44.130
competition is misunderstood.

02:58:44.490 --> 02:58:46.190
They think that perfect

02:58:46.200 --> 02:58:50.320
competition is something like

02:58:50.330 --> 02:58:52.840
absolutely harsh, ruthless

02:58:52.940 --> 02:58:54.520
competition.

02:58:54.580 --> 02:58:57.180
Actually nothing like that.

02:58:57.360 --> 02:58:59.520
The definition is very simple.

02:58:59.640 --> 02:59:02.800
Perfect competition is a market

02:59:02.810 --> 02:59:06.640
structure in which there are

02:59:06.650 --> 02:59:10.140
so many sellers and buyers that

02:59:10.150 --> 02:59:15.180
none of them can influence the

02:59:15.190 --> 02:59:18.140
market price by changing

02:59:18.150 --> 02:59:20.820
the volume of their

02:59:20.830 --> 02:59:23.080
supply or demand.

02:59:24.470 --> 02:59:26.370
The price of a product in a completely

02:59:26.380 --> 02:59:29.010
competitive market is determined by

02:59:29.020 --> 02:59:32.070
the interaction of thousands of independent

02:59:32.080 --> 02:59:36.190
buyers and hundreds of independent sellers.

02:59:36.670 --> 02:59:38.450
Every buyer and every seller

02:59:38.460 --> 02:59:41.270
is a piece of sand on the scale

02:59:41.280 --> 02:59:44.230
of the market, which can not change

02:59:44.240 --> 02:59:47.130
anything in the market by

02:59:47.140 --> 02:59:48.990
its behavior.

02:59:49.390 --> 02:59:53.030
Let's look at the signs of

02:59:53.040 --> 02:59:54.690
perfect competition.

02:59:57.130 --> 02:59:59.230
Well, I actually said about the

02:59:59.240 --> 03:00:00.170
first sign.

03:00:00.250 --> 03:00:01.950
Here is a sign.

03:00:02.430 --> 03:00:04.010
Each of the very large numbers

03:00:04.020 --> 03:00:06.310
of sellers and buyers has such a

03:00:06.320 --> 03:00:08.910
small market share that they cannot

03:00:08.920 --> 03:00:11.070
change the market price by their

03:00:11.080 --> 03:00:14.310
behavior, but can sell or buy

03:00:14.320 --> 03:00:17.810
as many products as they want

03:00:17.820 --> 03:00:20.190
at that price.

03:00:23.580 --> 03:00:27.120
Let me give you an example, I think it

03:00:27.140 --> 03:00:29.160
will be appropriate.

03:00:29.600 --> 03:00:32.720
Here is a friend who lives

03:00:32.730 --> 03:00:35.540
in the Volgograd province, calls me in

03:00:35.550 --> 03:00:38.220
Moscow and asks what tomatoes in

03:00:38.230 --> 03:00:39.120
Moscow are for?

03:00:40.580 --> 03:00:43.280
The case was in the summer and not last

03:00:43.290 --> 03:00:46.560
year, I don't remember what I answered,

03:00:46.740 --> 03:00:48.820
well, let's say, 10 rubles per kilogram.

03:00:50.400 --> 03:00:52.440
She had an unfettered curiosity.

03:00:52.880 --> 03:00:55.780
She was going to bring a truck

03:00:55.790 --> 03:00:57.660
with Volga tomatoes to Moscow.

03:01:01.170 --> 03:01:02.770
So, what did she come from, having

03:01:02.910 --> 03:01:04.850
received my information, the price

03:01:04.860 --> 03:01:07.870
of tomatoes in Moscow 10 rubles per kilogram?

03:01:12.480 --> 03:01:15.520
It was based on the fact that

03:01:15.530 --> 03:01:17.380
if today the price is so, its appearance

03:01:18.140 --> 03:01:21.500
or not appearance on the

03:01:21.510 --> 03:01:25.520
market can not affect the price.

03:01:25.530 --> 03:01:31.250
But on the other hand, she is confident

03:01:31.630 --> 03:01:33.170
that since she holds a tiny

03:01:33.180 --> 03:01:35.230
share of the tomato market, she

03:01:35.240 --> 03:01:38.690
will be able to sell any quantity

03:01:38.700 --> 03:01:40.190
of her tomatoes at this price,

03:01:40.200 --> 03:01:41.670
10 rubles per kilogram.

03:01:43.200 --> 03:01:46.300
That is, and a ton, and three, and even

03:01:46.310 --> 03:01:48.380
five, and more, she just has no.

03:01:49.220 --> 03:01:51.480
It is clear that if she brought to

03:01:51.490 --> 03:01:54.120
Moscow at the same time, say,

03:01:54.130 --> 03:01:56.820
thousands of tons of tomatoes, then

03:01:56.830 --> 03:01:59.460
such a large seller would necessarily

03:01:59.470 --> 03:02:01.220
influence the market price.

03:02:01.820 --> 03:02:03.620
But that would no longer be a condition

03:02:03.630 --> 03:02:04.880
for perfect competition.

03:02:05.760 --> 03:02:08.160
Under perfect competition, market

03:02:08.170 --> 03:02:10.440
price is determined by the interaction

03:02:12.030 --> 03:02:14.610
of thousands of independent

03:02:14.620 --> 03:02:18.550
buyers, hundreds of independent

03:02:18.560 --> 03:02:21.070
sellers, each piece of

03:02:21.080 --> 03:02:24.310
sand on the general market

03:02:24.320 --> 03:02:26.930
scale, and no one alone

03:02:26.940 --> 03:02:28.710
can influence the price.

03:02:29.150 --> 03:02:31.290
Another example, so that it might

03:02:31.300 --> 03:02:32.790
be better understood.

03:02:33.910 --> 03:02:39.070
You encountered a neighbor at the entrance.

03:02:39.450 --> 03:02:42.250
He comes from the bazar.

03:02:43.310 --> 03:02:45.630
You ask him what tomatoes are for?

03:02:46.190 --> 03:02:49.930
He responds, 10 rubles per kilogram.

03:02:51.190 --> 03:02:53.550
So what are you coming from?

03:02:53.810 --> 03:02:56.230
How soon did that price come up?

03:02:57.290 --> 03:02:59.910
Your appearance or not appearing

03:02:59.920 --> 03:03:02.830
on the market as a buyer

03:03:02.840 --> 03:03:05.830
again can not affect the price.

03:03:06.470 --> 03:03:08.650
But you can buy at this price, for 10

03:03:08.660 --> 03:03:10.970
rubles, and a kilogram, and 3, and

03:03:10.980 --> 03:03:12.490
5, and even 10.

03:03:13.410 --> 03:03:15.810
That is, you also feel like

03:03:15.820 --> 03:03:17.770
a perfect competitor

03:03:17.780 --> 03:03:19.630
in the tomato market, but

03:03:19.640 --> 03:03:21.910
not as a seller, but as a buyer.

03:03:24.070 --> 03:03:26.210
Let's look at the schedule.

03:03:29.040 --> 03:03:32.560
Balanced market price and demand curve

03:03:32.570 --> 03:03:35.000
for a product of a particular firm.

03:03:35.160 --> 03:03:37.500
Look at two schedules.

03:03:38.620 --> 03:03:41.640
The left chart illustrates the demand

03:03:41.650 --> 03:03:43.300
for supply in a completely

03:03:43.310 --> 03:03:44.740
competitive market.

03:03:45.160 --> 03:03:47.040
I repeat again.

03:03:47.280 --> 03:03:50.240
There are thousands of buyers and hundreds

03:03:50.250 --> 03:03:52.160
of independent sellers.

03:03:52.480 --> 03:03:56.380
On the X-axis we place the total

03:03:56.390 --> 03:03:58.460
number of tomatoes sold and purchased

03:03:58.470 --> 03:04:00.220
on this market.

03:04:00.620 --> 03:04:01.440
And what do we see?

03:04:02.400 --> 03:04:06.580
That at the price P with the star

03:04:06.590 --> 03:04:10.420
we have some market balance.

03:04:10.840 --> 03:04:12.800
Demand on the tomato market

03:04:12.810 --> 03:04:14.940
from all buyers is equal to

03:04:14.950 --> 03:04:16.900
the supply on this market

03:04:16.910 --> 03:04:18.320
from all sellers.

03:04:19.160 --> 03:04:21.380
Now look at the right schedule.

03:04:21.660 --> 03:04:25.620
You see, on the X axis I postpone and

03:04:25.630 --> 03:04:27.580
indicate the output, production, volume

03:04:27.880 --> 03:04:29.440
of the cumal.

03:04:30.640 --> 03:04:33.720
It is a separate company.

03:04:34.000 --> 03:04:36.080
This is, in a way, my tomato

03:04:36.090 --> 03:04:37.500
acquaintance.

03:04:38.280 --> 03:04:41.160
If on the left chart the bill goes for

03:04:41.170 --> 03:04:43.740
thousands of tons, then on the right

03:04:43.750 --> 03:04:45.580
chart it only goes for tons.

03:04:46.280 --> 03:04:48.940
It is a sandstone on a market scale.

03:04:48.950 --> 03:04:52.620
And it takes the existing

03:04:52.630 --> 03:04:57.180
market price P with a star as a set.

03:04:57.840 --> 03:05:00.080
As economists say, it is

03:05:00.090 --> 03:05:05.060
a price-taker, the price recipient.

03:05:06.510 --> 03:05:08.330
She takes this price as

03:05:08.340 --> 03:05:10.850
a set and can sell any quantity

03:05:10.860 --> 03:05:14.530
of her tomatoes at that price.

03:05:16.610 --> 03:05:18.950
Note that in perfect competition,

03:05:18.960 --> 03:05:22.070
it cannot raise the

03:05:22.080 --> 03:05:23.430
price.

03:05:24.250 --> 03:05:26.710
No one will buy tomatoes.

03:05:26.950 --> 03:05:30.150
What's the point of having hundreds

03:05:30.160 --> 03:05:32.230
of sellers with a lower price?

03:05:32.970 --> 03:05:36.010
And it makes no sense to lower

03:05:36.330 --> 03:05:39.070
the price, because at this price

03:05:39.080 --> 03:05:41.170
she can sell any amount of

03:05:41.180 --> 03:05:41.950
her tomatoes.

03:05:43.280 --> 03:05:46.100
It was you and I who saw the first

03:05:46.110 --> 03:05:48.400
sign of perfect competition.

03:05:49.080 --> 03:05:52.420
Let us go back to our signs,

03:05:52.430 --> 03:05:55.900
let us look at the second sign.

03:05:56.440 --> 03:05:58.760
Full homogeneity of products,

03:05:58.920 --> 03:06:00.560
lack of trademarks.

03:06:01.520 --> 03:06:02.580
What does this mean?

03:06:04.150 --> 03:06:09.470
The products of different sellers

03:06:09.480 --> 03:06:11.610
are completely the same in

03:06:11.620 --> 03:06:13.050
the representation of buyers.

03:06:13.710 --> 03:06:16.830
Buyers do not distinguish the product

03:06:16.840 --> 03:06:19.310
of one seller from another and

03:06:19.320 --> 03:06:21.690
the seller himself from the other.

03:06:22.110 --> 03:06:23.670
But when you come to the real

03:06:23.680 --> 03:06:25.750
tomato market, agree, you will

03:06:25.760 --> 03:06:27.130
still walk in the rows, you

03:06:27.530 --> 03:06:28.530
will watch.

03:06:28.990 --> 03:06:30.910
Here, it seems tomatoes are

03:06:30.920 --> 03:06:33.850
red, but this seller seems

03:06:33.860 --> 03:06:36.310
to break a little confidence.

03:06:36.550 --> 03:06:38.630
This is not possible

03:06:38.640 --> 03:06:40.330
in perfect competition.

03:06:40.590 --> 03:06:44.390
All sellers on one person and all

03:06:44.400 --> 03:06:46.990
products are absolutely the same,

03:06:47.130 --> 03:06:48.150
no differences.

03:06:49.610 --> 03:06:52.550
Look at the third sign.

03:06:53.050 --> 03:06:55.470
Free entry and access

03:06:55.480 --> 03:06:57.730
to the market.

03:06:59.240 --> 03:07:02.560
This means that there are no barriers,

03:07:02.570 --> 03:07:05.200
financial, administrative,

03:07:05.340 --> 03:07:07.420
any, that prevented it from

03:07:07.430 --> 03:07:09.800
entering the market of new sellers

03:07:09.810 --> 03:07:13.260
or the departure of sellers

03:07:13.270 --> 03:07:15.180
from this market.

03:07:17.340 --> 03:07:20.940
Let us try this example for the

03:07:20.950 --> 03:07:23.980
discharge.

03:07:24.360 --> 03:07:27.860
Somewhere I read that our current

03:07:27.870 --> 03:07:31.020
president Vladimir Putin in his

03:07:33.390 --> 03:07:35.340
temporary, worked private transportation

03:07:35.350 --> 03:07:37.940
on his jigul.

03:07:38.200 --> 03:07:39.480
What did it mean?

03:07:39.960 --> 03:07:41.640
That he just one day sat down

03:07:41.650 --> 03:07:44.100
at the wheel of his car, went

03:07:44.500 --> 03:07:45.920
to the streets of St. Petersburg,

03:07:45.930 --> 03:07:49.000
that is, entered the private

03:07:49.010 --> 03:07:50.400
market.

03:07:52.100 --> 03:07:54.640
A while later, Vladimir Vladimirovich

03:07:54.650 --> 03:07:56.820
found an interesting job

03:07:56.830 --> 03:07:59.260
as President of Russia.

03:07:59.440 --> 03:08:02.300
This means only that he quietly

03:08:02.310 --> 03:08:04.000
put his jigguls in the garage

03:08:04.010 --> 03:08:06.380
and went to work in the Kremlin.

03:08:06.600 --> 03:08:08.820
As easily he entered the market,

03:08:08.830 --> 03:08:11.860
so easily he left it.

03:08:12.140 --> 03:08:14.280
This is a sign of perfect competition.

03:08:14.540 --> 03:08:16.660
There are no barriers to entry

03:08:16.670 --> 03:08:17.300
and exit.

03:08:19.880 --> 03:08:21.380
The fourth sign.

03:08:21.740 --> 03:08:24.700
Perfect knowledge of the market

03:08:24.710 --> 03:08:28.360
by sellers and buyers.

03:08:28.540 --> 03:08:31.580
Again, if you come to the real

03:08:31.590 --> 03:08:36.300
tomato market, then you'll

03:08:36.310 --> 03:08:38.980
probably walk in the rows,

03:08:39.300 --> 03:08:40.580
again, looking.

03:08:40.820 --> 03:08:42.960
Maybe there are tomatoes

03:08:42.970 --> 03:08:45.640
better or a little cheaper.

03:08:47.170 --> 03:08:48.430
This is not possible in

03:08:48.440 --> 03:08:49.550
perfect competition.

03:08:50.330 --> 03:08:55.050
All sellers and all buyers are there.

03:08:55.330 --> 03:08:58.250
They seem to be together at one point.

03:08:58.330 --> 03:09:00.410
All market information

03:09:00.420 --> 03:09:03.130
is instantly disclosed.

03:09:03.430 --> 03:09:05.910
It is equally available to

03:09:05.920 --> 03:09:07.670
all sellers and all buyers.

03:09:09.220 --> 03:09:13.640
Well, if you summarize all that

03:09:13.650 --> 03:09:16.240
I said, you will probably

03:09:16.380 --> 03:09:18.960
agree that perfect competition

03:09:18.970 --> 03:09:21.860
is abstraction.

03:09:23.020 --> 03:09:27.480
Such a market does not really exist.

03:09:27.640 --> 03:09:31.280
There are markets that are more or

03:09:31.290 --> 03:09:34.880
less close to this ideal, but there

03:09:34.890 --> 03:09:35.960
is no perfectly competitive

03:09:35.970 --> 03:09:37.360
market in reality.

03:09:39.130 --> 03:09:39.710
Then the question.

03:09:40.850 --> 03:09:42.690
If there are no competitive

03:09:42.700 --> 03:09:45.550
markets, why study them?

03:09:46.230 --> 03:09:48.290
The answer is very simple.

03:09:48.510 --> 03:09:51.690
For the same reason that the chemist

03:09:51.700 --> 03:09:53.550
studies the properties of, for

03:09:54.090 --> 03:09:55.890
example, absolutely pure distilled

03:09:55.900 --> 03:09:58.550
water, which nature does not exist either.

03:09:59.690 --> 03:10:03.230
It is simply impossible to understand

03:10:03.240 --> 03:10:06.050
the properties of any impurities unless

03:10:06.060 --> 03:10:09.630
we understand, not study the subject in

03:10:09.640 --> 03:10:10.610
some perfect state.

03:10:10.620 --> 03:10:13.810
I was talking about the first type of

03:10:13.910 --> 03:10:15.910
market, perfect competition.

03:10:16.650 --> 03:10:20.030
The second type of market is called monopoly.

03:10:22.050 --> 03:10:23.430
Read the definition.

03:10:24.250 --> 03:10:25.890
Monopoly is a market structure

03:10:25.900 --> 03:10:29.490
in which there is only one company

03:10:29.500 --> 03:10:33.070
in the market that produces

03:10:33.290 --> 03:10:37.350
a product that has no close

03:10:37.360 --> 03:10:38.410
substitute.

03:10:41.700 --> 03:10:44.410
Monopolies are found at

03:10:44.420 --> 03:10:47.950
the national, regional, most often

03:10:47.960 --> 03:10:51.190
at the local level.

03:10:51.510 --> 03:10:53.370
In Russia there are national

03:10:53.380 --> 03:10:55.590
monopolies.

03:10:55.890 --> 03:10:59.750
In particular, after the reform

03:10:59.760 --> 03:11:03.070
of RAUIS, the federal network

03:11:03.080 --> 03:11:05.970
company will monopolize

03:11:05.980 --> 03:11:08.590
the power transmission lines.

03:11:10.170 --> 03:11:13.210
Or, say, in our country,

03:11:14.720 --> 03:11:16.730
it is a national monopoly,

03:11:17.070 --> 03:11:21.030
or, say, in our city there is

03:11:21.040 --> 03:11:25.250
only one company offering certain

03:11:25.260 --> 03:11:26.130
services.

03:11:26.670 --> 03:11:29.050
It is a monopoly on the local.

03:11:30.970 --> 03:11:33.810
But the next market structure

03:11:33.820 --> 03:11:37.330
is more common - oligopoly.

03:11:39.520 --> 03:11:40.500
What is it?

03:11:40.800 --> 03:11:42.060
See the definition.

03:11:42.460 --> 03:11:45.700
Oligopoly is a market structure

03:11:45.710 --> 03:11:49.100
characterized by a small

03:11:49.110 --> 03:11:52.780
number of operating firms.

03:11:56.690 --> 03:11:58.350
Examples of oligopoly.

03:12:00.830 --> 03:12:02.830
Two airlines on one

03:12:02.840 --> 03:12:03.750
route.

03:12:04.590 --> 03:12:07.750
In Moscow, the mobile market is controlled,

03:12:07.760 --> 03:12:10.950
if I am not mistaken, by four

03:12:11.690 --> 03:12:12.810
companies.

03:12:12.890 --> 03:12:16.090
Oligopoly is defined as a situation where there

03:12:16.100 --> 03:12:20.390
are less than 20 companies in the market.

03:12:20.630 --> 03:12:21.430
This is considered

03:12:21.440 --> 03:12:23.530
an oligopolistic structure.

03:12:23.870 --> 03:12:25.950
This is a very common case

03:12:25.960 --> 03:12:28.290
of oligopoly.

03:12:29.610 --> 03:12:32.270
Oligopoly is a very interesting

03:12:32.280 --> 03:12:33.250
market structure.

03:12:36.450 --> 03:12:38.150
When we looked at

03:12:38.160 --> 03:12:40.310
perfect competition,

03:12:40.320 --> 03:12:44.330
we saw that when a single

03:12:44.340 --> 03:12:47.650
seller makes a decision,

03:12:47.660 --> 03:12:49.990
he does not look at

03:12:50.000 --> 03:12:52.630
other sellers.

03:12:53.010 --> 03:12:54.790
He is a sandstone on the scale of the

03:12:54.800 --> 03:12:56.470
market, he simply accepts the

03:12:56.480 --> 03:12:58.570
market price.

03:12:58.650 --> 03:13:01.190
The monopoly does not look at competitors,

03:13:01.200 --> 03:13:03.330
either, for the simple reason

03:13:03.340 --> 03:13:05.330
that they simply do not exist in

03:13:05.340 --> 03:13:06.070
the monopoly.

03:13:06.270 --> 03:13:11.550
But the olegopolist acts as his

03:13:12.210 --> 03:13:16.210
own capabilities and the behavior

03:13:16.220 --> 03:13:19.730
of other firms allow him.

03:13:21.640 --> 03:13:24.040
The olegopolistic situation

03:13:24.050 --> 03:13:26.320
is similar to a kind of card game

03:13:26.330 --> 03:13:31.540
where there is no single pre-

03:13:31.550 --> 03:13:33.380
set model of behavior.

03:13:33.820 --> 03:13:36.740
Each player plays as the

03:13:36.750 --> 03:13:40.780
cards are allowed and as the

03:13:40.790 --> 03:13:42.540
competitors play.

03:13:43.180 --> 03:13:45.160
In the context of oligopoly,

03:13:45.170 --> 03:13:48.760
strategic behavior is formed.

03:13:51.430 --> 03:13:56.730
At the same time, individual olegopolists

03:13:56.740 --> 03:13:59.030
can choose one or another form of

03:13:59.040 --> 03:14:01.470
rivalry, one or another strategy

03:14:01.480 --> 03:14:04.770
of rivalry or adopt a strategy

03:14:04.780 --> 03:14:07.810
of conspiracy.

03:14:07.830 --> 03:14:08.930
So happens too.

03:14:11.840 --> 03:14:14.320
The fourth type of market

03:14:14.330 --> 03:14:16.460
is monopolistic competition.

03:14:17.240 --> 03:14:18.580
Read the definition.

03:14:19.320 --> 03:14:21.780
Monopolistic competition is a

03:14:21.790 --> 03:14:24.500
market structure in which

03:14:24.510 --> 03:14:27.600
a group of goods that are close

03:14:27.610 --> 03:14:29.560
substituents are produced

03:14:29.600 --> 03:14:32.180
by a large number of independent

03:14:32.190 --> 03:14:34.660
firms.

03:14:35.060 --> 03:14:36.000
Try to explain.

03:14:38.260 --> 03:14:40.360
Let us remember the perfect

03:14:40.370 --> 03:14:42.560
competition.

03:14:43.820 --> 03:14:46.620
There were a lot of firms there.

03:14:47.940 --> 03:14:50.380
In theory, it is infinite.

03:14:51.440 --> 03:14:54.480
In the conditions of monopolistic

03:14:54.490 --> 03:14:56.980
competition, may not be so

03:14:56.990 --> 03:14:58.440
many, but also very many.

03:14:58.940 --> 03:15:02.120
But there are fundamental differences.

03:15:02.560 --> 03:15:04.680
Remember, I said that in perfect

03:15:04.690 --> 03:15:09.020
competition, the products of individual

03:15:09.030 --> 03:15:11.780
firms are absolutely indistinguishable

03:15:11.790 --> 03:15:14.720
in the eyes of the buyers.

03:15:14.980 --> 03:15:17.020
The companies are completely the same.

03:15:17.340 --> 03:15:19.300
This is not the case

03:15:19.310 --> 03:15:20.900
with monopolistic competition.

03:15:21.160 --> 03:15:25.840
Here, each company has a certain distinction

03:15:25.850 --> 03:15:30.720
that distinguishes it, its products

03:15:30.730 --> 03:15:35.140
or its own from other firms.

03:15:38.680 --> 03:15:45.140
It is a mini monopoly.

03:15:45.700 --> 03:15:48.380
It is a mini-monopoly in a very narrow

03:15:48.390 --> 03:15:50.960
segment of the market.

03:15:50.970 --> 03:15:51.740
Here is example.

03:15:52.460 --> 03:15:55.900
There are many cafes in our city, but

03:15:55.910 --> 03:16:00.180
I distinguish this cafe from what.

03:16:00.660 --> 03:16:02.820
Maybe it's a cafe, I think, maybe

03:16:02.830 --> 03:16:05.240
it's a better place to eat in this

03:16:05.250 --> 03:16:07.060
cafe, maybe there's a more

03:16:07.070 --> 03:16:09.480
sympathetic waitress, maybe the

03:16:09.490 --> 03:16:11.900
interior is more attractive, or

03:16:11.910 --> 03:16:13.120
maybe this cafe is just

03:16:13.130 --> 03:16:15.000
located closer to my home.

03:16:16.550 --> 03:16:20.200
That is, in the conditions

03:16:20.210 --> 03:16:22.640
of monopolistic competition, I repeat

03:16:22.650 --> 03:16:26.900
again, individual firms, possessing

03:16:27.300 --> 03:16:29.580
some distinctive features,

03:16:29.590 --> 03:16:32.140
possess a small but still

03:16:32.150 --> 03:16:34.160
monopolistic power in

03:16:34.170 --> 03:16:36.600
a narrow segment of the

03:16:36.610 --> 03:16:37.780
market.

03:16:39.230 --> 03:16:42.700
And now look, it is necessary

03:16:42.710 --> 03:16:46.460
to distinguish between pure

03:16:46.470 --> 03:16:52.240
monopoly and monopoly power.

03:16:53.060 --> 03:16:55.900
Monopoly power arises where

03:16:56.640 --> 03:17:00.560
a single firm has some

03:17:00.570 --> 03:17:02.960
control over the price.

03:17:07.750 --> 03:17:11.510
It can change the price within

03:17:11.520 --> 03:17:15.050
certain limits.

03:17:16.610 --> 03:17:18.970
This is not the case with perfect competition.

03:17:19.390 --> 03:17:22.890
Please look at the left schedule.

03:17:23.370 --> 03:17:25.010
On the left is a very competitive

03:17:25.020 --> 03:17:26.970
company.

03:17:27.350 --> 03:17:29.750
I have already said that in perfect

03:17:29.760 --> 03:17:32.570
competition, a single firm,

03:17:32.580 --> 03:17:35.830
being a sandstone on the general

03:17:35.840 --> 03:17:38.130
market scale, can sell

03:17:38.140 --> 03:17:40.290
any quantity of its products

03:17:40.300 --> 03:17:43.430
at the market price.

03:17:43.730 --> 03:17:46.770
The function of demand for a product

03:17:46.780 --> 03:17:49.390
of a completely competitive company

03:17:49.400 --> 03:17:51.670
is a horizontal line.

03:17:52.050 --> 03:17:56.150
The market can buy any quantity

03:17:56.160 --> 03:17:59.190
of its products at the current

03:17:59.200 --> 03:18:01.130
market price.

03:18:01.910 --> 03:18:03.790
Changing the price of a completely

03:18:03.800 --> 03:18:06.310
competitive company cannot by definition.

03:18:07.130 --> 03:18:08.670
But a firm with a monopoly

03:18:08.680 --> 03:18:11.110
power may change the price to

03:18:11.120 --> 03:18:13.170
a greater or lesser extent.

03:18:13.350 --> 03:18:15.750
Please look at the right schedule.

03:18:15.890 --> 03:18:17.810
There, the demand function for the

03:18:17.820 --> 03:18:20.470
company's product has a negative slope.

03:18:23.220 --> 03:18:26.520
This means that the company can

03:18:26.530 --> 03:18:28.980
raise or lower the price.

03:18:28.990 --> 03:18:33.560
But it is clear that by raising the

03:18:33.660 --> 03:18:35.600
price, it will face a decrease in

03:18:35.610 --> 03:18:37.440
demand for its product.

03:18:38.600 --> 03:18:43.160
And if the price is lower, it will face its increase.

03:18:43.660 --> 03:18:46.420
No super monopoly can abolish

03:18:46.430 --> 03:18:49.560
the laws of demand.

03:18:49.570 --> 03:18:53.840
But what is obvious is that it is important

03:18:53.850 --> 03:18:58.480
that the more the slope of demand

03:18:58.490 --> 03:19:02.740
for a company's product, the lower

03:19:02.750 --> 03:19:04.880
its monopoly power.

03:19:06.280 --> 03:19:11.780
So I have just said that by the inclination

03:19:11.790 --> 03:19:15.580
of the demand function on a firm'

03:19:15.590 --> 03:19:19.120
s product, one can judge how

03:19:19.130 --> 03:19:21.400
great its monopoly power is.

03:19:32.230 --> 03:19:33.170
Well, please look at the quantity of the

03:19:33.550 --> 03:19:34.770
goods, as always, the price of the goods,

03:19:37.520 --> 03:19:41.640
and let's say the function of demand

03:19:41.650 --> 03:19:43.800
is going like this.

03:19:47.780 --> 03:19:49.650
Look what it means.

03:19:49.690 --> 03:19:51.990
You see, the function has a

03:19:52.000 --> 03:19:53.210
fairly high tilt.

03:19:58.440 --> 03:20:03.320
So, a firm can raise the price quite

03:20:03.330 --> 03:20:06.820
significantly from P0 to P1, see,

03:20:07.000 --> 03:20:09.060
a significant price increase, without

03:20:09.070 --> 03:20:13.440
fear of losing a large volume

03:20:13.450 --> 03:20:14.420
of demand.

03:20:24.960 --> 03:20:29.040
In other words, it is difficult for the consumer

03:20:29.050 --> 03:20:31.460
to do without the product of this company.

03:20:32.100 --> 03:20:35.180
Even with a large price rise, the

03:20:35.190 --> 03:20:38.620
fall in demand will be minor.

03:20:39.800 --> 03:20:42.800
We say that the company

03:20:42.810 --> 03:20:45.520
has a high monopoly power.

03:20:47.450 --> 03:20:49.670
Now imagine a monopoly

03:20:49.680 --> 03:20:51.910
competitive company.

03:20:52.610 --> 03:20:55.750
The function of demand for its product goes

03:20:55.760 --> 03:20:57.570
very much by logo.

03:21:02.910 --> 03:21:06.710
So, the company can raise the price.

03:21:06.730 --> 03:21:09.730
This is the demand function for its product.

03:21:10.070 --> 03:21:12.010
But note, the company has

03:21:12.330 --> 03:21:16.050
raised the price very slightly.

03:21:17.190 --> 03:21:19.210
How much did you lose in demand?

03:21:22.170 --> 03:21:23.330
very much.

03:21:23.590 --> 03:21:27.170
A slight price increase has led

03:21:27.180 --> 03:21:29.770
to a significant decline in demand.

03:21:29.780 --> 03:21:30.630
Why so?

03:21:31.450 --> 03:21:33.510
In the context of monopolistic

03:21:33.520 --> 03:21:36.170
competition, the product

03:21:36.180 --> 03:21:38.490
has many substitutes.

03:21:39.130 --> 03:21:41.490
Therefore, with a slight increase

03:21:41.500 --> 03:21:45.250
in the price, buyers can easily switch

03:21:45.260 --> 03:21:50.370
to the product of other companies.

03:21:52.100 --> 03:21:53.540
What extreme case?

03:21:53.720 --> 03:21:57.520
The perfect competition.

03:21:57.800 --> 03:22:01.020
When the line of demand for the

03:22:01.030 --> 03:22:05.220
company's product becomes such a slope

03:22:06.560 --> 03:22:10.640
that it becomes horizontal.

03:22:11.580 --> 03:22:13.600
The company has no

03:22:13.610 --> 03:22:15.560
control over the market

03:22:15.570 --> 03:22:16.920
price.

03:22:17.140 --> 03:22:21.740
He can only accept the price.

03:22:21.750 --> 03:22:27.560
Now let us look at the reasons

03:22:27.880 --> 03:22:30.220
why monopoly power

03:22:30.230 --> 03:22:34.180
can arise and exist.

03:22:34.540 --> 03:22:38.440
I identify three reasons.

03:22:38.580 --> 03:22:40.760
The first reason is very simple.

03:22:40.820 --> 03:22:43.000
Exclusive rights

03:22:43.010 --> 03:22:45.400
granted by authorities.

03:22:47.260 --> 03:22:50.000
Well, let's say, local

03:22:50.010 --> 03:22:53.240
or regional authorities,

03:22:53.250 --> 03:22:56.500
or all-Russian authorities, only my

03:22:56.510 --> 03:22:59.640
firm is allowed to engage in this

03:22:59.650 --> 03:23:00.620
type of activity.

03:23:01.300 --> 03:23:03.580
Other companies simply do not

03:23:03.590 --> 03:23:05.480
get the appropriate license.

03:23:06.800 --> 03:23:10.580
This leads to an administrative

03:23:10.590 --> 03:23:12.740
monopoly.

03:23:12.860 --> 03:23:17.860
If the license is granted to several

03:23:17.870 --> 03:23:23.080
companies, we are given an administrative oligopoly.

03:23:23.520 --> 03:23:26.320
Now let us talk about the second reason

03:23:26.330 --> 03:23:30.040
for the existence of monopoly power.

03:23:30.940 --> 03:23:33.640
It is the exclusive ownership

03:23:33.650 --> 03:23:36.140
of any production resource.

03:23:36.540 --> 03:23:39.160
I have said many times that

03:23:39.170 --> 03:23:41.500
to do something, you need

03:23:41.760 --> 03:23:42.880
resources.

03:23:43.560 --> 03:23:45.500
Imagine, please, that some important

03:23:45.510 --> 03:23:48.140
resource for the production

03:23:48.150 --> 03:23:52.380
of this product is in the

03:23:52.390 --> 03:23:54.420
exclusive property

03:23:54.430 --> 03:23:57.440
of this firm.

03:23:57.960 --> 03:23:59.980
Only she can produce

03:23:59.990 --> 03:24:01.540
this product.

03:24:01.550 --> 03:24:03.800
Others can't, and our company

03:24:03.810 --> 03:24:06.920
is a monopolist.

03:24:07.640 --> 03:24:08.420
The example.

03:24:10.840 --> 03:24:13.440
Alcoa was once the monopoly

03:24:13.450 --> 03:24:16.820
on the American aluminum

03:24:16.830 --> 03:24:18.700
market.

03:24:19.020 --> 03:24:21.280
Her monopoly was based on

03:24:21.290 --> 03:24:23.580
the fact that she alone

03:24:23.590 --> 03:24:26.040
owned all the bacit fields

03:24:26.050 --> 03:24:27.420
in Chile.

03:24:29.360 --> 03:24:33.580
Only a surgeon can perform

03:24:33.590 --> 03:24:35.680
this operation.

03:24:36.500 --> 03:24:42.260
He is the monopolist of his talent.

03:24:42.560 --> 03:24:44.480
Only he has the teaching talent,

03:24:44.490 --> 03:24:47.420
and on this basis there

03:24:47.430 --> 03:24:49.700
is a monopoly.

03:24:53.920 --> 03:24:58.360
Or only this company has a patent

03:24:58.370 --> 03:25:00.300
on the latest technological

03:25:00.310 --> 03:25:02.000
development.

03:25:02.480 --> 03:25:05.980
It is becoming a monopoly.

03:25:06.300 --> 03:25:09.020
If a resource belongs to

03:25:09.030 --> 03:25:11.460
several firms, it is no longer

03:25:13.660 --> 03:25:17.560
a monopoly, but an oligopoly.

03:25:21.520 --> 03:25:24.620
The third reason for monopoly power

03:25:24.630 --> 03:25:29.160
is the increasing return on scale.

03:25:30.340 --> 03:25:31.500
Here it is a little more difficult.

03:25:32.700 --> 03:25:36.560
Let us remember what is

03:25:36.570 --> 03:25:40.300
increasing return on scale.

03:25:40.520 --> 03:25:42.160
What does she mean?

03:25:42.760 --> 03:25:43.960
When does it emerge?

03:25:44.000 --> 03:25:46.120
When do we talk about increasing

03:25:46.130 --> 03:25:47.660
scale?

03:25:51.960 --> 03:25:54.640
When the number of resources

03:25:54.650 --> 03:25:57.820
used increases by N times, production

03:25:57.830 --> 03:26:01.520
increases by more than

03:26:01.530 --> 03:26:03.220
N times.

