So I lost the first ruble,

04:38:19.250 --> 04:38:20.840
and I won the second 8.

04:38:21.340 --> 04:38:23.260
The total limit income is

04:38:23.270 --> 04:38:24.140
only 7.

04:38:25.100 --> 04:38:27.480
The price is above the limit income.

04:38:30.870 --> 04:38:34.290
And it can be strictly proved, I do not

04:38:34.300 --> 04:38:35.310
use higher mathematics, but simply

04:38:35.330 --> 04:38:36.070
standing on my fingers to explain,

04:38:36.080 --> 04:38:39.770
it can be strictly proved that if the demand

04:38:40.070 --> 04:38:44.050
function is nine, the function of the

04:38:44.150 --> 04:38:46.110
monopolist's limit income is also

04:38:46.120 --> 04:38:48.670
linear, and its inclination is twice

04:38:48.680 --> 04:38:51.310
the inclination of the demand

04:38:53.090 --> 04:38:55.700
function, the prileasing function

04:38:55.710 --> 04:38:56.760
of demand.

04:38:57.600 --> 04:39:00.820
The margin income function is also linear,

04:39:00.830 --> 04:39:03.460
written on a slide, and its slope

04:39:03.470 --> 04:39:07.320
is twice the slope of the demand curve.

04:39:07.940 --> 04:39:08.720
Here, we see that.

04:39:08.960 --> 04:39:10.420
See the demand function.

04:39:10.460 --> 04:39:13.040
Do you see the limit income function?

04:39:13.050 --> 04:39:14.980
The function of the limit income is twice

04:39:14.990 --> 04:39:17.580
as fast as the function of demand.

04:39:18.120 --> 04:39:20.940
Its inclination is twice as much.

04:39:23.070 --> 04:39:24.390
Well, and now let's see with

04:39:27.300 --> 04:39:29.730
you how you can show on the

04:39:29.740 --> 04:39:33.430
chart of achieving monopoly balance.

04:39:35.370 --> 04:39:36.490
Here what do we see?

04:39:37.230 --> 04:39:39.290
linear function of demand.

04:39:41.630 --> 04:39:44.690
On the other hand, we see the function

04:39:44.700 --> 04:39:45.610
of the limit income.

04:39:46.900 --> 04:39:48.860
The function of the limit income has, as

04:39:48.880 --> 04:39:50.580
I have said, a twice greater inclination

04:39:50.590 --> 04:39:52.920
than the function of the demand for

04:39:52.930 --> 04:39:54.620
the monopoly product.

04:39:54.900 --> 04:39:58.380
And I also put on this picture the functions,

04:39:58.390 --> 04:40:01.000
the classic functions of the marginal

04:40:01.010 --> 04:40:04.320
and average income of the monopolist.

04:40:04.420 --> 04:40:06.660
Excusions, the marginal costs

04:40:06.670 --> 04:40:09.200
of the monopoly and its average

04:40:09.210 --> 04:40:10.240
total costs.

04:40:10.620 --> 04:40:12.800
The function of the marginal,

04:40:12.810 --> 04:40:14.940
I repeat, and the average total cost

04:40:14.950 --> 04:40:16.180
of the monopoly.

04:40:19.840 --> 04:40:22.400
The rules, I said, are always one.

04:40:23.720 --> 04:40:26.220
Profit is maximum at such volume

04:40:26.230 --> 04:40:30.100
of production, where the limit

04:40:32.070 --> 04:40:36.650
income is equal to the limit costs.

04:40:37.870 --> 04:40:42.190
Look at the schedule where we

04:40:42.200 --> 04:40:44.590
cross the functions of the limit

04:40:44.600 --> 04:40:45.870
income and the limit cost.

04:40:46.210 --> 04:40:47.390
You see the crossroads?

04:40:49.810 --> 04:40:54.490
This point determines the QM issue,

04:40:55.770 --> 04:40:59.430
in which the profit of the monopoly is maximum.

04:41:03.070 --> 04:41:06.090
What price will the monopoly pay?

04:41:07.860 --> 04:41:13.220
This price should be looked for on the function on

04:41:13.230 --> 04:41:15.320
the demand curve.

04:41:15.380 --> 04:41:17.880
See, we restore the perpendicular

04:41:17.980 --> 04:41:23.100
from the QM point up to the intersection

04:41:23.110 --> 04:41:26.140
with the demand function.

04:41:26.360 --> 04:41:29.240
And from there we lower the perpendicular to the

04:41:29.250 --> 04:41:30.720
Y axis, to the price axis.

04:41:32.380 --> 04:41:37.960
So, in order to sell QM goods,

04:41:38.460 --> 04:41:40.880
the monopoly must set the PM price

04:41:40.890 --> 04:41:42.980
for its products.

04:41:45.620 --> 04:41:49.340
At this price and such volume of

04:41:49.350 --> 04:41:51.760
production and sales, the profit

04:41:51.770 --> 04:41:55.040
of the monopolist becomes maximum.

04:41:57.680 --> 04:41:59.100
And now finally, please,

04:41:59.920 --> 04:42:04.240
can you show the profit, the

04:42:04.250 --> 04:42:06.280
amount of monopoly profit

04:42:06.290 --> 04:42:07.820
on the chart?

04:42:10.090 --> 04:42:11.650
Well look at.

04:42:11.930 --> 04:42:13.770
What is profit, remember.

04:42:13.930 --> 04:42:14.650
It is easy.

04:42:15.390 --> 04:42:17.710
Profit is the difference between

04:42:17.720 --> 04:42:20.470
revenue and total costs.

04:42:23.590 --> 04:42:25.470
What is profit and revenue?

04:42:29.150 --> 04:42:34.310
This is the price multiplied by the volume of sales.

04:42:36.010 --> 04:42:39.390
So PM multiplied by QM.

04:42:39.650 --> 04:42:41.450
Graphically, this is the area

04:42:41.460 --> 04:42:48.910
of the rectangle O PM EQM.

04:42:52.470 --> 04:42:54.910
Where are the total costs?

04:42:56.850 --> 04:42:58.250
The total cost can be calculated

04:42:58.260 --> 04:43:01.490
by multiplying the average total

04:43:01.500 --> 04:43:04.410
cost again by the volume of

04:43:04.420 --> 04:43:05.650
production.

04:43:06.270 --> 04:43:09.810
If so, then the average total

04:43:09.820 --> 04:43:13.270
cost is equal to the area of the

04:43:13.280 --> 04:43:21.090
rectangle O C FQM.

04:43:22.840 --> 04:43:24.260
That is, it is the area of the

04:43:26.670 --> 04:43:28.940
lower rectangle, and how do we get the profit?

04:43:29.080 --> 04:43:30.060
From the area of the

04:43:30.070 --> 04:43:31.300
upper rectangle, we deduct the area

04:43:31.310 --> 04:43:32.640
of the lower rectangle.

04:43:32.880 --> 04:43:33.740
Accordingly, the profit of the

04:43:33.750 --> 04:43:35.760
monopoly is equal to the area

04:43:35.770 --> 04:43:40.820
of the rectangle C PM E F.

04:43:47.370 --> 04:43:49.890
And a very important conclusion that

04:43:49.900 --> 04:43:51.430
follows from all this.

04:43:52.110 --> 04:43:54.370
Let us remember the perfect competition.

04:44:00.030 --> 04:44:04.110
In perfect competition, the price

04:44:04.120 --> 04:44:06.410
at which the company sells its

04:44:08.380 --> 04:44:11.270
products becomes equal to

04:44:11.280 --> 04:44:14.470
its limit costs at the

04:44:14.480 --> 04:44:16.590
point of balance.

04:44:16.650 --> 04:44:21.150
There is the equation P equal to MC.

04:44:23.200 --> 04:44:25.660
And in the conditions of monopoly domination,

04:44:27.060 --> 04:44:29.440
the monopoly sets a price, look

04:44:31.570 --> 04:44:33.900
at the figure, above the

04:44:33.910 --> 04:44:35.160
limit costs.

04:44:36.320 --> 04:44:37.800
See you?

04:44:38.160 --> 04:44:41.740
The demand line is above the limit

04:44:41.750 --> 04:44:42.780
cost curve.

04:44:45.430 --> 04:44:48.590
The monopoly's limit costs at the QM issue

04:44:48.600 --> 04:44:51.450
are equal to the OC segment.

04:44:52.770 --> 04:44:55.190
The price of the monopolist, the price that the

04:44:55.200 --> 04:44:57.270
monopolist has set, is equal to the

04:44:57.280 --> 04:44:58.570
OPM segment.

04:45:00.210 --> 04:45:01.910
So, I repeat, the monopoly

04:45:02.090 --> 04:45:03.490
sets a price that exceeds

04:45:03.510 --> 04:45:05.530
the limit costs.

04:45:06.950 --> 04:45:10.330
And hence the most important conclusion is that

04:45:10.340 --> 04:45:18.170
monopolies are able to overpriced the price and underestimate

04:45:18.180 --> 04:45:20.130
the volume of production.

04:45:20.690 --> 04:45:23.410
In the conditions of monopoly power, the

04:45:23.670 --> 04:45:28.350
price is higher and the output is lower

04:45:28.360 --> 04:45:31.730
than in the conditions of competition.

04:45:33.110 --> 04:45:38.090
This is the main claim of society

04:45:38.100 --> 04:45:39.290
to monopoly.

04:45:41.150 --> 04:45:46.190
Monopolies overpriced the price and underestimated

04:45:46.200 --> 04:45:47.950
the volume of production compared to the

04:45:47.960 --> 04:45:49.790
volume of production that would have been

04:45:49.800 --> 04:45:51.710
made if it had had had instead of the

04:45:51.720 --> 04:45:52.790
monopoly competition.

04:45:54.880 --> 04:45:57.620
This is the main basis

04:45:57.630 --> 04:46:00.920
for antimonopoly

04:46:00.930 --> 04:46:03.000
policy.

04:46:06.400 --> 04:46:09.420
Antimonopoly policy is a policy

04:46:09.430 --> 04:46:12.300
of promoting competition.

04:46:14.680 --> 04:46:18.180
In the West, anti-monopoly policy has

04:46:18.190 --> 04:46:23.720
more than a century of experience.

04:46:24.420 --> 04:46:26.660
The first anti-monopoly law in the

04:46:26.670 --> 04:46:28.640
United States, if I am not mistaken,

04:46:28.650 --> 04:46:31.100
was passed in the 1990s of the

04:46:31.110 --> 04:46:33.520
19th century.

04:46:33.800 --> 04:46:37.540
We are in Russia 100 years later.

04:46:38.500 --> 04:46:41.100
Details about the anti-monopoly

04:46:41.110 --> 04:46:45.340
policy are stated in the text of

04:46:45.350 --> 04:46:47.540
this lecture, attached to this

04:46:47.550 --> 04:46:49.280
visual course.

04:46:49.820 --> 04:46:54.440
I will say two words literally that

04:46:54.450 --> 04:46:57.300
antimonopoly policy is a policy

04:46:57.310 --> 04:47:00.400
of promoting competition.

04:47:01.800 --> 04:47:03.520
It is for this it is directed.

04:47:06.910 --> 04:47:10.630
In Russia, a new anti-monopoly

04:47:10.640 --> 04:47:12.810
law has been adopted.

04:47:13.030 --> 04:47:16.450
In 2006, the Competition Protection

04:47:16.460 --> 04:47:17.890
Act was adopted.

04:47:18.490 --> 04:47:21.210
A very useful law contains

04:47:21.220 --> 04:47:23.150
many interesting provisions,

04:47:23.160 --> 04:47:25.630
new provisions that aim to

04:47:25.640 --> 04:47:27.330
prevent monopoly

04:47:27.340 --> 04:47:29.450
domination in the markets.

04:47:33.220 --> 04:47:36.820
But on the other hand, our policy in

04:47:36.830 --> 04:47:39.040
Russia, the policy of the Russian

04:47:39.050 --> 04:47:41.180
government, in this sense, is

04:47:41.190 --> 04:47:42.700
at least ambiguous.

04:47:43.620 --> 04:47:46.800
On the one hand, a very useful anti-

04:47:46.810 --> 04:47:49.040
monopoly law is being adopted.

04:47:50.260 --> 04:47:55.900
More and more large companies

04:47:55.910 --> 04:47:58.780
are being created under

04:47:58.790 --> 04:48:00.540
state control.

04:48:02.190 --> 04:48:05.150
The so-called national champions.

04:48:08.470 --> 04:48:11.510
On the one hand, we are fighting against monopoly.

04:48:11.670 --> 04:48:15.670
On the other hand, we are developing monopoly.

04:48:17.250 --> 04:48:20.370
Rosoboronexport is pulling in its

04:48:20.380 --> 04:48:21.330
entire orbit.

04:48:21.340 --> 04:48:23.430
All new and new enterprises

04:48:23.440 --> 04:48:28.490
form holdings under their control.

04:48:28.790 --> 04:48:31.890
The same is happening in aviation.

04:48:33.600 --> 04:48:35.360
I repeat, you will read more about this

04:48:35.370 --> 04:48:37.940
in the text of the lecture.

04:48:41.260 --> 04:48:44.380
I would only like to be careful

04:48:44.390 --> 04:48:47.780
to question the effectiveness of

04:48:47.790 --> 04:48:49.040
such a policy.

04:48:53.660 --> 04:48:57.560
Most foreign experts and domestic

04:48:57.570 --> 04:49:00.360
experts believe that the policy

04:49:00.660 --> 04:49:03.900
of state support for large

04:49:03.910 --> 04:49:09.060
companies will only lead

04:49:09.070 --> 04:49:11.580
to the fact that these companies

04:49:11.590 --> 04:49:14.640
will become ineffective.

04:49:15.220 --> 04:49:17.000
State support, lack of

04:49:17.120 --> 04:49:19.620
competition will kill business.

04:49:22.560 --> 04:49:24.620
Read more about this in the text

04:49:24.630 --> 04:49:26.040
of the lecture.